"description": "<p>Required Skills:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2+ years of NetSuite experience required</li>\n<li>Experience with SuiteScript, SuiteTalk, SuiteFlow, SuiteBuilder, and SuiteBundles</li>\n<li>Bachelor's degree in computer science, or equivalent knowledge</li>\n<li>Proven and very strong project management skills in managing multiple projects</li>\n<li>Expert in JavaScript, and JQuery</li>\n<li>Excellent attention to detail and knowledge of coding/application design best practices</li>\n<li>Excellent ability to communicate with diverse groups of users and developers</li>\n<li>Excellent leadership and organizational skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Bonus Points:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience in using Eclipse</li>\n<li>Experience with Application integration (SOAP, RESLET, JSON, API Integration, Web services.)</li>\n<li>Experience with other cloud based platforms (Salesforce, Intact)</li>\n<li>ExtJS or similar Javascript framework experience a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Architect solutions to meet customer requirements and document statements of work</li>\n<li>Work within a team environment to ensure project success</li>\n<li>Build custom solutions and web based applications on the NetSuite platform using Javascript libraries.</li>\n<li>Test, document and demonstrate developed solutions both internally and externally</li>\n<li>Participate in the ongoing development of technical, design and best practices</li>\n<li>Continue NXTurn’s history of delivering success.</li>\n<li>Work with the Business to help refine requirements and create solutions for complex business processes</li>\n<li>Create SuiteScripts and Workflows for customization's</li>\n<li>Create Custom forms, fields, and searches</li>\n<li>Update and maintain workflows and SuiteScripts</li>\n<li>Work with third party SuiteApps to maintain and enhance current capabilities</li>\n<li>Work with NetSuite Support to maintain the support cases opened for Business needs</li>\n<li>Support enterprise-wide reporting efforts</li>\n<li>Document customizations and any system modifications</li>\n<li>Own responsibility for ongoing technical development of IT resources on NetSuite projects</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Perks:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This is a great opportunity to join a fast growing team with room for growth and advancement. We sell, implement, customize and integrate the fastest selling cloud ERP system in the world.</li>\n<li>Paid Holidays, Vacation, Health Insurance</li>\n<li>Training reimbursement</li>\n<li>Bonuses</li>\n<li>Flexible Schedule</li>\n<li>Remote workers consider</li>\n</ul>\n<p>About Us:</p>\n<p>Our company is a full service Netsuite 5 Star Partner that provides consulting, implementation and support for clients nationwide. Netsuite is the leading provider of on-demand, integrated business management software for growing and midsize businesses.  You will be part of a team of developers supporting our clients in areas of CRM, ERP, Ecommerce, and Customer Support. NXTurn has been a top five NetSuite partner for the past 6 years. Our team members are creative thinkers, passionate problem solvers, and willing to do whatever it takes to deliver the capabilities our customers require.</p>\n<p>Recruiters, please don't contact this job poster. Domestic full time employment only - no offshore firms or outsourcing.</p>\n<p>Please do not contact job poster about other services, products or commercial interests.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.nxturn.com/about-us/careers/\">http://www.nxturn.com/about-us/careers/</a></p>\n",
