"company": "Thornburg Investment Management",
"company_url": null,
"location": "Santa Fe, NM ",
"title": "Senior Application Developer",
"description": "<p>Thornburg Investment Management is a privately owned global investment firm offering a range of solutions for investors around the world. Founded in 1982 and headquartered in Santa Fe, NM, we manage U.S. mutual funds, separate accounts for high-net-worth investors and institutional accounts, and UCITS funds for non-U.S. investors.</p>\n<p>At Thornburg, it’s more than what we do; it’s how we do it. A flexible perspective built on collaboration and cross-pollination of ideas, an unconventional approach to portfolio construction, and a reputation of integrity are important aspects of how we do business. Far from the groupthink of Wall Street, Thornburg is positioned to offer a different point of view and a broader frame of reference in our global search for relative value opportunities.</p>\n<p>The Senior Application Developer will join a dynamic team within the information technology department developing and supporting critical business applications.</p>\n<p>REQUIRED SKILLS/KNOWLEDGE:</p>\n<p>5 years of professional experience developing and supporting web, client and service applications using C#, ASP.Net, WPF, HTML, JavaScript, CSS, and Microsoft SQL Server database technologies\n5 years of professional experience building, integrating and troubleshooting software components\nKnowledge of IT environments including networking, server technologies, databases, security, testing, performance and deployment\nProven ability to assess existing systems and make technical recommendations that scale and meet product owner expectations\nProfessional experience using source control including branching and merging\nProfessional experience using issue and project tracking software\nProven ability to establish requirements and gauge priorities through discussions with clients and team members\nThe ability to produce technical documentation as well as end-user guidelines\nThe ability to communicate effectively and work well in a team environment</p>\n<p>DESIRED SKILLS/KNOWLEDGE:</p>\n<p>Previous experience in the financial services industry\nExperience with continuous integration, automated build and release management\nFamiliarity with WordPress\nPHP development experience\nThe ability to understand, design and describe complex database structures\nCapable of curating, analyzing and validating data sets\nExperience developing unit and program test plans</p>\n<p>PERSONAL CHARACTERISITICS:</p>\n<p>The ability to work as part of a team, which may be established for a chartered project or as part of ongoing daily assignments within the department\nHighly motivated to learn new programming languages and technologies\nMust be accountable and detail oriented with excellent communication skills, both oral and written\nCommitment to complete assignments according to established goals and objectives\nAbility to work non-business hours as needed</p>\n<p>Santa Fe is the capital of New Mexico. Founded in 1610 and nicknamed “The City Different,” Santa Fe captures hearts and minds with its museums, restaurants, theater, opera, and adobe-style architecture. With an average of over 300 sunny days per year and picturesque landscape, it’s no wonder that outdoor activities such as skiing and hiking in “The Land of Enchantment” attract visitors from around the world.</p>\n<p>Thornburg believes that diversity and inclusivity are vital to positive long-term success for our strategies and the firm’s broader business outcomes. We are proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applications receive consideration for employment without regard to race, creed, color, religion, sex, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, marital status, national origin, disability, age, or veteran status. The firm provides annual progress reports to the investment management team, shareholders, and executive management to highlight multiple diversity and inclusivity metrics and continually work to bring awareness to the importance of this issue.</p>\n",
"how_to_apply": "<p>Please apply online at: <a href=\"https://chu.tbe.taleo.net/chu02/ats/careers/v2/viewRequisition?org=THORNBURG&amp;cws=40&amp;rid=409\">https://chu.tbe.taleo.net/chu02/ats/careers/v2/viewRequisition?org=THORNBURG&amp;cws=40&amp;rid=409</a></p>\n",
