"url": "https://jobs.github.com/positions/9f96041e-99bb-4718-b9cb-257a2b0e1c83",
"created_at": "Mon Feb 25 13:27:26 UTC 2019",
"company": "BCG Platinion WESA ",
"company_url": "https://bcgplatinion.com/global/",
"location": "LONDON",
"title": "Lead Software Engineer",
"description": "<p>As a seamlessly integrated part of the BCG network, we provide consulting services focused on the development and implementation of business-critical IT architecture and digital solutions. Our areas of expertise range from IT architecture design to digital transformation and implementation management. We create technology platforms and deliver exceptionally customized solutions of the future for our clients, from data strategies to next-generation customer journey solutions and transformational business models. We solve the most daunting challenges that companies face today and envision for tomorrow. Our style is entrepreneurial – nimble and innovative, with multifaceted, cross-functional teams and completely vendor-independent. Our unique selling proposition is technology expertise and delivery excellence.</p>\n<p>Our mission is to support our clients’ digital transformation with short-term and sustained solutions to the most complex and time-sensitive challenges; while collaborating with clients to transform visionary strategies into leading-edge technology platforms and impact at scale.</p>\n<p>BCG Platinion was founded in 2000. Since then, we have grown continuously and successfully. Today we have offices in Europe, North and South America, South Africa as well as Asia Pacific.In 2017, we acquired MAYA Design, a Pittsburgh-based digital design and innovation lab, allowing us to accelerate our digital capabilities through human-centered design. Working organically across disciplines and across BCG, we offer a unified and unrivaled package that combines strategy work with hands-on expertise.</p>\n<p>At BCG Platinion we are looking for full-stack Lead Engineers to lead solutions design, development and implementation of Minimum Viable Products (MVPs) for clients within multiple industries, as they transform into digital space. Our ideal candidates will have a combination of consulting experience, solutions architecture and core engineering experience within web applications, mobile optimized solutions, some data analytics experience, and cloud, and they’ll use those skills to create beautiful, state of the art products for our clients.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Participate in ideation and brainstorming sessions to devise creative and disruptive digital solutions</li>\n<li>Build digital apps, APIs and data solutions to drive digital transformation projects</li>\n<li>Promote agile principles and methodology</li>\n<li>Work on multiple client prototypes at the same time and facilitate client demo</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n<li>BS or MS in Computer Science or equivalent professional experience</li>\n<li>At least 6 years of professional software development experience within the enterprise or consumer market</li>\n<li>Agile development in a production environment at a startup or enterprise organization</li>\n<li>Mid-level to expert experience within one or more of the following: ES6/ES5, React, React Native, Node, Angular, JQuery and Javascript, Python, Scala or Java</li>\n<li>Solid API skills (e.g. Express/Node, GraphQL/Relay, Flask, Jersey, Java Spring REST or WebApi2)</li>\n<li>Hands-on RDBMS experience (data modeling, analysis, programming, stored procedures)</li>\n<li>CSS, motion design and usability experience</li>\n<li>Foundation in data structures, algorithms, and OO Design with rock-solid programming skills</li>\n<li>Proven success working in and promoting a rapidly changing, collaborative, and iterative product development environment</li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal skills, analytical skills, combined with intellectual curiosity, and a desire and ability to \"get things done\" are essential</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Nice-to-Have Experience</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Data science and visualization (Hadoop, Spark, Databricks, Drill, Tableau)</li>\n<li>Predictive analytics and machine learning (scikit-learn, Tensorflow, Mahout, recommendation systems)</li>\n<li>NoSQL databases and modeling (Cassandra &amp; MongoDB)</li>\n<li>Scaled apps in the cloud: Amazon AWS EC2, Google Computer Engine</li>\n<li>iOS: Objective-C or Swift</li>\n<li>Work experience in one or more of the following industries: FinTech, Insurance, Pharmaceutical, Health Care, Retail, Telecom, Luxury Brands</li>\n</ul>\n",
"how_to_apply": "<p>Email resume to <a href=\"mailto:PLALONRecruiting@bcg.com\">PLALONRecruiting@bcg.com</a></p>\n",
