"description": "<p>Does C++, gaming and building software for other developers sound sweeter than a bag of candy?</p>\n<p>Would you like to continue your saga in a core technology team which develops the SDK that powers all of the King games, running on 260 million devices?</p>\n<p>The purpose: Developing our Unified Platform to help the King organization build games in a super-easy way on a global level!</p>\n<p>Ready to level up?</p>\n<p><strong>Your role within our Kingdom</strong></p>\n<p>Your new team consists of 30 amazing Kingsters, including developers, tech writers, build engineers, POs &amp; QA's, and by joining this fab team will enable you to make such a great contribution on the game developers ´user experience.</p>\n<p>Being part of a fluid, techy and inclusive environment means that together we celebrate releases, arrange knowledge sharing sessions (Fika &amp; Learn!) and play games (of course). Oh, and since SDK is the ruling champions of the internal \"Robot building challenge\" you´ll need to be a solid Lego-builder. No pressure.</p>\n<p>Skills to create thrills</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fluent in modern C++ (C++ 11 and later)</li>\n<li>Platform development, API design or Software DevKits and tools development</li>\n<li>Cross-platform development (especially iOS and Android)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Bonus points</p>\n<ul>\n<li>GIT</li>\n<li>CMake</li>\n<li>Experience of setting up test automation</li>\n<li>Unity game engine experience</li>\n<li>We know that you are in to games on some level (casual, console, board-games, Uno etc.) and if you also have experience working in the online gaming industry, we´d sure like to hear your story!\nA great saga needs all sorts of heroes</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Making games is fun! Especially when you do it with people who share the same idea of what makes a good workplace, great. We design games for everyone, no matter where they are or who they are, and we employ all sorts of people from all kinds of backgrounds to bring them to life. Truth is, we simply can’t expect diversity in our players and originality in our games without first nurturing it in our people. A great saga needs all sorts of heroes. And that’s it.</p>\n<p><strong>We’re Seriously Playful</strong></p>\n<p>We believe that great gaming experiences happen when they are developed by working in small, autonomous creative teams that control the whole process - from idea to amazing products. Our close connection with the player community gets us instant feedback and enables us to deliver truly magical moments. We value your free time and your need to refuel, relax and find inspiration - by playing games with your colleagues, being at home with your family or going to the gym or out for a run. That's how we stay creative!</p>\n",
